UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc3='From the desk of the esteemed Archmage Ansirem Runeweaver$B' WHERE word_id = 126381;
UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc3='I prithee not think ill of my making light of the situation, but we shant be seeing Apprentice Argoly around any longer. Archmage Ataeric has been rushing his students through training and sending me thick-skulled nincompoops who can scarcely conjure their own drink! If I\'m to expect these buffoons to do the work of skilled magi, then woe that this boy couldn\'t handle a simple errand.$B' WHERE word_id = 126382;
UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc3='I prithee not think ill of my making light of the situation, but we shant be seeing Apprentice Argoly around any longer. Archmage Ataeric has been rushing his students through training and sending me thick-skulled nincompoops who can scarcely conjure their own drink! If I\'m to expect these buffoons to do the work of skilled magi, then woe that this boy couldn\'t handle a simple errand.$B' WHERE word_id = 126382;
UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc3='The grasses in Alterac are hearty and impart a strong, earthy flavor to hot tea. I sent the boy foraging around the outskirts of the floating city to find fresh grass. It slipped my mind that he never came back, as I was busied with correcting yet another bumbling apprentice who\'d set fire to a 200-year-old tapestry.$B' WHERE word_id = 126383;
UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc3='It is known that Altera herbs produce an excellent aromatic additive to tea. I sent this young man to the walls of the soaring city, so that he collected some fresh plants for me, and completely ignored his prolonged absence, for he was busy repairing a two-hundred-year tapestry that was set on fire by another blunt-headed student.' WHERE word_id = 126930;
UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc3='It struck me that Argoly had grinned like a fool when I presented him the task, but I shooed him away to his work. I finally had my answer this morning when I sent my attendant down to the surface to retrieve an important memo I\'d lost to the breeze while gazing over the frozen wastes below us. She returned hurriedly to inform me that Argoly\'s remains were found in a broken slump on the tundra.$B' WHERE word_id = 126384;
UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc3='Now I remember the stupid smirk of Argoli when I received this assignment, and I understand that I made the mistake of sending him with this assignment. The mystery of the disappearance of the student was revealed this morning, when I sent down my messenger for an important note that I dropped, pondering near the window. The messenger returned with the sad news that the remains of Argoli were found on the rocks below.' WHERE word_id = 126931;
UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc3='I\'d no doubt of the boy\'s hand in his own demise when I found a folded pouch of Felweed tucked into his robes. It would seem that Argoly took my invitation to "go get some grass" quite literally, and busied himself with chewing it before setting to work on my task. The rest, I trust, you can gather on your own.$B' WHERE word_id = 126385;
UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc3='When I found a folded bundle of felts among his robes, I had no last doubt that the unfortunate himself was guilty of his doom. Obviously, he literally embraced my call to "get some grass" and chewed a bit of shit before leaving for the assignment. The rest you can guess yourself.' WHERE word_id = 126932;
UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc3='<This flier was recently pasted here. Residue of glue on the stone shows that many fliers have previously occupied this location.>' WHERE word_id = 126386;
UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc3='Hark!$B$BMagic is not what you have been taught. Its dangers far exceed the greatest gifts it may bring! Question your Elders, that you may know the truth. Act now while there is time to save yourselves! Learn the ways of Nature and share in the balance of all things, ere your destructive ways upset it beyond repair.$B$B<An unfamiliar seal decorates the bottom of the flier.>' WHERE word_id = 126387;
